Sentencas: Chemical stability of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) as an electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was investigated.
Titulo: The effect of reduction atmosphere on the LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: At low oxygen-partial pressure (0.003 atm), the LSGM electrolyte partly decomposed due to the development of high overpotentials, and thus the induced reduction atmosphere near cathode.
Titulo: The effect of reduction atmosphere on the LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The morphology of LSGM grain near cathode changed due to the formation of new phases.
Titulo: The effect of reduction atmosphere on the LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The main decomposition phases were La2O3, La(OH)(3) and LaSrGaO4.
Titulo: The effect of reduction atmosphere on the LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The polarization conductance increased due to the microstructural change in LSM and thus the increase in the specific area of the LSM electrode.
Titulo: The effect of reduction atmosphere on the LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell
